title: Flight Simulator 2020 - POI's - France - Saint-Nazaire Bridge
description:
In this video we will fly under the Saint-Nazaire Bridge. The Saint-Nazaire Bridge (French: Le pont de Saint-Nazaire) is a cable-stayed bridge spanning the river Loire and linking Saint-Nazaire on the north bank and Saint-Brevin-les-Pins on the south bank, in the department of Loire-Atlantique, Pays de la Loire, France. The bridge is crossed by the "Route bleue" (RD213).

The cable-stayed metallic structure measures 720 m and, including the access viaducts, represents a total length of 3 356 m.
